  "created": "2025-10-13",
  "description": "The ubiquitin-proteasome system (UPS) is the primary pathway for selective protein degradation in eukaryotic cells. This process involves the covalent attachment of ubiquitin chains to target proteins through an enzymatic cascade (E1, E2, E3), recognition of polyubiquitinated substrates by the 26S proteasome, and ATP-dependent proteolysis. The system regulates cell cycle progression, signal transduction, transcription, and protein quality control. Substrate specificity is determined by E3 ubiquitin ligases, which recognize degrons (degradation signals) in target proteins. The process demonstrates computational logic in protein fate determination and cellular homeostasis.",
  "id": "yeast_ubiquitin_proteasome",
